Package com.bonitasoft.test.toolkit.model

Interface Document

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArchivedDocumentProxy, DocumentProxy
    public interface Document
    A Bonita document is defined as a process data on the process definition, and can be set and updated during the execution of the process.

    • Method Summary

    • Method Detail

      • getId

        String getId()
        Returns:
        The ID of the document.

      • getName

        String getName()
        Returns:
        The name of the document, defined in the process definition.

      • getFileName

        String getFileName()
        Returns:
        The filename of the value of the document, a file uploaded during the execution of the process.

      • getSubmittedBy

        User getSubmittedBy()
        Returns:
        The User that submitted the value of this document.

      • getVersion

        String getVersion()
        Returns:
        The version of this document: each time a document is updated, its version is incremented.

      • getContent

        byte[] getContent()
        Returns:
        The content of this document, or null if isInternal() returns false;

      • isInternal

        boolean isInternal()
        A Bonita document is considered as internal if its content is stored on the Bonita database. A document referenced by an URL is not internal.
        Returns:
        true if the document is internal.

      • getUrl

        String getUrl()
        Returns:
        The URL to retrieve the content of the document, or null if isInternal() returns true.

      • isArchived

        boolean isArchived()
        Returns:
        true if the document is archived.
